For installing Docker on Windows, please follow below steps -

Step 1: Download the Linux kernel update package (WSL 2). Download WSL 2 from below URL and set WSL 2 to run Docker on Windows
        https://wslstorestorage.blob.core.windows.net/wslblob/wsl_update_x64.msi

Step 2: Install Linux kernel update package (WSL 2) which you downloaded in previous step.

Step 3: Now open powershell with run as administrator and below commands which will enable WSL 2.

	wsl --set-default-version 2
	
	for e.g. check my console output what you will see when you run above command-

	PS C:\Windows\system32> wsl --set-default-version 2
	For information on key differences with WSL 2 please visit https://aka.ms/wsl2
	The operation completed successfully.

Step 4: Now download Docker from below URL -
	https://desktop.docker.com/win/main/amd64/Docker%20Desktop%20Installer.exe

Step 5: Install Docker which you downloaded in previous step.

Step 6: Now restart your PC/Laptop.

Step 7: If you are getting any error in Docker then you can restart docker service from powershell using below command.

	restart-service *docker*
